criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. 65 years of age and older;

          2. identify as a man;

          3. English speaking; and

          4. demonstrate readiness for physical activity (by the PAR‐Q+ questionnaire or a letter
             of recommendation from their physician)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. performed ≥75 minutes of moderate‐to‐vigourous intensity physical activity during the
             past week;

          2. participated in any strength training in the past 3 months;

          3. participated in any aerobic exercise class in the past 3 months;

          4. live in a nursing home or assisted living facility; or

          5. have plans to be out of town for more than 7 days during the 12‐week intervention
             period.
